text.paragraph:
Dosage reductions may need to be considered for adult 
                           patients with hepatic impairment, and geriatric patients [see Warnings and Precautions (5.7), Use in Specific Populations (8.6), Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
                           ].

Adverse reaction information is derived from the two trials for procedural sedation [see 
                              Clinical Studies (14.2)
                           ] in which 318 adult patients received dexmedetomidine hydrochloride. The mean total dose was 1.6 mcg/kg (range: 0.5 to 6.7), mean dose per hour was 1.3 mcg/kg/hr (range: 0.3 to 6.1) and the mean duration of infusion of 1.5 hours (range: 0.1 to 6.2).  The population was between 18 to 93 years of age, ASA I-IV, 30% ≥ 65 years of age, 52% male and 61% Caucasian.

Although dexmedetomidine hydrochloride is dosed to effect, it may be necessary to consider dose reduction in subjects with hepatic impairment [see 
                              Dosage and Administration (2.2), Warnings and Precautions (5.7)
                           ].
